Common - EN:
There is a 3x3 grid board. A marker is placed in the top left corner. At any given point, the marker has two legal moves:
1. Move down one square;
2. Move right one square;
The marker cannot move diagonally. The marker cannot move up or left.
How many distinct paths can the marker take to reach the bottom right corner?

